          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1714735880619-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>lime zest</strong>, <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and grind to a paste –<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>tom yum paste</strong></p><p>Tip: Don’t have a pestle & mortar? Pulse in a food processor!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1714735909490-x200.jpg",
